casebody.data:
William S. MacFarlane, Respondent, v. Thomas H. Walter, Appellant. Decided May 24, 1889. Appeal from order directing judgment for plaintiff on demurrer as frivolous. W. T. Birdsall, for appellant. F. E. Anderson, for respondent.

Before Sedgwick, Ch. J., and Freedman, J.

Per Curiam.

Order affirmed with $10 costs.
